Mediator takes responsbility for communication between a group of objects.
It acts as router between objects.
Decouples co-dependent objects.
Centralizes control logic.

Use when interdependent objects form difficult-to-understand structure. BEEN THERE!

May not be appropriate if there's a lot of sub-classing.

Examples
-> Air traffic control: Airplane-OtherAirplanes-Airport
-> House: Hitting snooze turns on coffee maker
-> Coordinate related GUI components
-> Timer class schedule methods
-> Concurrency Executor method
-> JMS uses Mediator and Observer to allow applications to subscribe and publish data

